result.name: Barista Jam

reviews.text:
I bumped into Barista Jam by chance as I was walking in Hong Kong Soho. It is unassuming, small but it has great atmosphere inside. As a matter of fact, if you are not paying attention, you may miss it. I went in and order some coffee and pastries. The coffee was one of the best I had in Hong Kong, and HK has many coffee places ;-)
The pastries were also quite good, more of a French style rather than local. The only drawback is that the place is quite small and popular so you may not get a place to sit. But if you are looking for a great cup of coffee or expresso, I highly recommend Barista Jam.
One of the best cafe in town. Both hand drip and espresso based coffee are both delicious. Super helpful, coffee passionate and knowledgable staffs!! 💕
Here I can feel passion about their coffees. Full of taste and professional skills. Nice selection and variaties of sweet balanced cakes. Love it!!
Great cup of coffee. Had an Ethiopian bean in a pour over. Best cup of hot I've had in Hong Kong.

Good service, good subdued hip vibe... Pleasant!
Great coffee service and experience 👍🏼.

reviews.text: 來這裡點餐要先背熟你的下單內容，改出前一丁講慢左一少少，就會被姐姐 jip 你...

午餐: 瑞士汁雞脾炒蛋撈公仔麵、奶茶。
炒蛋好好食! 瑞士汁撈麵味道正。雖然略覺雞脾肉有d乾身，但勝在夠入味!
侍應粗聲粗氣，落單又慢。感覺唔多良好。食物好一般。

食物質素好， 價錢中等。
特別要讚佢嘅炒滑蛋，一流。 夠滑，仲有豐富蛋汁。 質地剛好，唔會太乾，又唔會太濕。 👍 

而座位舒適度一般，始終茶餐廳，而且多人食， 都算可接受嘅
2 公婆起身食 d 野，未食得落好多，點完等緊時，就有說話聽，d staff 又話慳家咩又七，你有最低消費就出聲，又無出聲，餐牌又無寫。我嚟食野，吾係背脊骨落有說話聽。
